File: platform/mcp-server/src/file-watcher.ts

Three locations need error handlers:

1. watchPlugin() at line 466: `const distWatcher = watch(distDir, ...)` — add `distWatcher.on('error', ...)` after creation, before `watchers.push(distWatcher)`.

2. watchPendingPlugin() at line 421: `const distWatcher = watch(distDir, ...)` — same pattern.

3. startConfigWatching() at line 527: `fw.configWatcher = watch(configDir, ...)` — add `fw.configWatcher.on('error', ...)` after creation.

The error handler pattern should be:
```ts
distWatcher.on('error', (err) => {
  log.warn(`File watcher: Error on dist watcher for "${pluginName}": ${err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err)}`);
  distWatcher.close();
});
```

For the config watcher, use 'config' as the label instead of pluginName.

Import `log` from './logger.js' is already present at line 25.

Note: After closing the watcher, mtime polling (already running as a fallback via startMtimePolling) will continue to detect changes, so no additional recovery is needed.

File: platform/mcp-server/src/browser-tools/analyze-site/detect-apis.ts

The bug: WebSocket endpoints are created from HTTP upgrade requests, so their normalized URL uses `https://` origin (e.g., `https://example.com/ws`). But WebSocket frame URLs use `wss://` scheme, so `new URL('wss://example.com/ws').origin` produces `wss://example.com`. The comparison `normalizedFrameUrl !== ep.url` on line 456 always fails for this scheme mismatch.

Fix approach: Create a small helper function (e.g., `normalizeWsUrl`) that converts WebSocket schemes to their HTTP equivalents:

```ts
const normalizeWsUrl = (url: string): string => {
  try {
    const parsed = new URL(url);
    if (parsed.protocol === 'wss:') parsed.protocol = 'https:';
    else if (parsed.protocol === 'ws:') parsed.protocol = 'http:';
    return `${parsed.origin}${parsed.pathname}`;
  } catch {
    return url;
  }
};
```

Apply this normalization in two places:
1. Line 416-423 in the grouping loop: when the protocol is 'websocket', use `normalizeWsUrl(req.url)` instead of `parsed.origin + parsed.pathname`
2. Lines 449-456 in the frame matching loop: use `normalizeWsUrl(frame.url)` instead of the current `parsedFrame.origin + parsedFrame.pathname`

Alternatively, apply it only in the frame matching loop (both to frame URL and endpoint URL) — this is simpler and equivalent since the normalization is only needed for comparison.

